<TD vAlign=top width=200><FONT face="Verdana, Arial" size=1>If you're an ISP or a "Start-up" wireless ISP looking for a total "last mile" solution to reach your customers via broadband, Northern Wireless products and solutions is your best choice.</FONT></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></DIV></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE></FONT></B></P>
<P><B><FONT face=Verdana,Arial color=#006da9 size=1></FONT></B>&nbsp;<FONT color=#cc3300><B><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>Overview</FONT></B><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1><B> </B></FONT></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>As an ISP you need a broadband last mile solution. You need a system that is more practical and cost-effective than traditional options, such as&nbsp; DSL and cable. Go broadband wireless access with Northern Wireless.</FONT> </P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>Broadband wireless access is faster, easier and cheaper to deploy than any alternate solution. By choosing our solution we can have your customers using wireless broadband&nbsp;in a matter of days.&nbsp;Your network can be scaled to demand.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>There are many technology choices to choose from once you have made the decision to go wireless for your last mile solution. Let Northern Wireless take the complexity out of your decision making. With our proven experience we can guide you in the right direction. Why reinvent the wheel, we have already experienced the growing pains in going wireless and we want to share our experience with you.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>We recommend only and 802.11b (Wifi) and some 80211a standard equipment for outdoor network. These standards are developed by the IEEE, the same working groups that implemented Ethernet (802.3). We provide only Wifi certified equipment to ensure interoperability with all equipment in our solution. Wifi certified products are the most common and least expensive equipment on the market.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>Some wireless suppliers recommend equipment that operates in a licensed spectrum that&nbsp;forces the ISP to purchase a license to operate in that frequency. Since it's not that simple&nbsp;to buy a license, the masses purchase the 802.11a or 802.11b license free equipment, thus the lower the prices.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>M</FONT><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>any wireless suppliers will sell a solution that requires proprietary equipment. (equipment is only available by that supplier) The initial solution may seem a fair price but customer premise expansion is costly and it is difficult negotiate lower prices. </FONT><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>By choosing Northern Wireless as your supplier for your system you can feel comfortable that you are not saddled with proprietary equipment . We use open standard Wifi equipment only.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial color=#ff9900 size=1><B>What we can do for you!</B></FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>Most of you have probably already investigated your options and know that you need wireless as its the only real affordable solution for your project. Somehow you need to get the project rolling and you are not an expert in the field. We can kick start you right now.</FONT></P>
<P><FONT face=Verdana,Arial size=1>Find out if there is any tower space for lease. Investigate the possible locations of potential tower sites. You need to pull out a topographical map of your community and mark up the coverage areas (where your customers are) and tower location information. Mark the estimated quantity of potential customers in the grids on the map. Scan the coverage area into your computer and email it to <A href="mailto:jcox@nwon.com">jcox@nwon.com</A>&nbsp;or fax to 613-843.9244. Upon receipt of the above information we can provide a preliminary design and pricing.</FONT></P></TD>
